Key Match Events: Morocco beat Congo-Brazzaville 6-0 in the World Cup African Qualifiers on June 11, 2024.
Goals were scored by Azeddine Ounahi (8'), Chadi Ryad (16'), Ayoub El Kaabi (20', 39', 53'), and Soufiane Rahimi (62').
Miscellaneous Highlights: Victory takes Morocco to the top of Pool E with 9 points.
Morocco's previous wins were against Tanzania (0-2) and Zambia (2-1).
